    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just seems like you're saying any form of nationalist sentiment is basically a countdown to conflict. but some people argue that without that strong sense of identity, people lose their connection to their community and a country just falls apart into chaos or becomes too fragmented to govern. isn't there a real risk of losing social stability if we stop prioritizing the national interest?",
